                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65460"><name nymRef="#Πρᾶτις">Πρᾶτις</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64775"><name nymRef="#Λέντιχος" type="patronymic">Λεντίχω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Pratis fils de Lentikhos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Pratis son of Lentichos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Pratis figlio di Lentichos.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The Thorns' probable attribution to the North Necropolis is due to the fact that the Italian archaeologists before World War II were mainly interested 
                    by this one.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
